@node introduction "CaLL maTTa BbS ++48-22-314328..................22-16"



	Thiz iz the ultimate WB game 4 all you traderz out there. However,
even if you are not a trader ya can play it too. If i'm not wrong thiz iz
the first "scene-like" wb game made. Maybe ya have never heard of our
group, that doesn't bother me really. It only means yer a sucka. OK. End of
crap...

@endnode

@node about "CaLL maTTa BbS ++48-22-314328..................22-16"


	There is no need to explain da rulez of thiz game as everyone
knows'em really. The only specific thing ya gonna find in thiz version 
is the amazing joystick AND mouse control.  
So to start the game you have to press yer red button on the joy or press
LMB. However thiz iz useless 2 say coz everyone who can read can read it
in the scroll.right. Now, to pause the game to flag yer n -0 warez press 
red button again. OK. Now, in thiz version we have the special crap 
things fallin' down, nothin' more about them coz they're explained 
on the main screen.
	NEW GREAT OPTION: NOW YOU CAN MOVE MINI'S WINDOW TO ANY SCREEN YOU
LIKE !!!! 	
	Feel the power of 100% pure assembler. HMMM...nothin' more 2 say. 

@endnode

@node bugs "CaLL maTTa BbS ++48-22-314328..................22-16"

	There are no known bugz in thiz version. The game works fine on all
machine's we have tested:
		
		- a1200 4fast
		- a500 2.0 kick 1mb
		- a500 1.3 1mb
		- a2000 2630/882/4mb

	If ya have any bug reports call the ultimate coolness harbour:

			maTTa BBS ++48-22-314328 22-16 

@endnode

@node future "CaLL maTTa BbS ++48-22-314328..................22-16"

		Future will only bring more tooltypes, more levels.
	Probably that's all. How much can you do to an arcanoid? :)

@endnode

@node tooltypes "CaLL maTTa BbS ++48-22-314328..................22-16"

	TOOLTYPES go as folows:

	DO NOT WAIT - self explanatory
	TOOLPRI - same as above
	TOOLWINDOW - where do you want the window
	JOYSPEED - funny things happen when you set it to minus value
	FLASH ON ERROR - hope thats clear
	MINIMUM BITPLANES - it sucks to have it on 1 bitplane

@endnode

